Date: Tue, 9 Aug 2016 14:40:07 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] configure: test for posix_spawn() in librt

As uclibc-ng puts posix_spawn() in librt, force its use when checking for
the function.

Signed-off-by: Eric Le Bihan <eric.le.bihan.dev@free.fr>
---
 configure | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/configure b/configure
index a638a89..e2dfee5 100755
--- a/configure
+++ b/configure
@@ -480,7 +480,7 @@ EOF
   choose cl openat OPENAT 'openat()'
   choose cl linkat LINKAT 'linkat()'
   choose clr pipe2 PIPE2 'pipe2()'
-  choose cl posixspawn POSIXSPAWN 'posix_spawn()'
+  choose cl posixspawn POSIXSPAWN 'posix_spawn()' -lrt
   choose clr ppoll PPOLL 'ppoll()'
   choose cl revoke REVOKE 'revoke()'
   choose cl sendfile SENDFILE 'sendfile()'
